# Tell PulseAudio to ignore the omap-hdmi-audio ALSA card.
#
# The HDMI card IS the real mainline omap-hdmi-audio (SND_SOC_OMAP_HDMI, platform
# device omap-hdmi-audio.1.auto) — NOT a driver stub. Its PCM open returns
# -EINVAL and PA's auto-profile probe fails ("Failed to find a working profile")
# because it needs an AUDIO-CAPABLE HDMI sink, and the display currently attached
# (a Philips 190C monitor) is DVI-class: its EDID is a 128-byte base block with
# NO CEA-861 extension, so no audio data block, so the HDMI link runs DVI mode
# with no audio path. That is CORRECT behaviour for that sink, not a bug.
#
# => HDMI audio out very likely WORKS on a real audio-capable sink (TV / AV
# receiver) with no code change, but this is UNTESTED — we have no audio-capable
# HDMI display to confirm it (verified 2026-07-07 via EDID; see the audio-outputs
# bring-up note). Keep this PULSE_IGNORE regardless: on a DVI monitor the card is
# unusable, and even on a TV routing desktop audio out HDMI is not what this
# speaker appliance wants by default (the TAS5713 speaker is the sink). If HDMI
# audio is ever wanted as a selectable output, drop this rule after confirming
# the card opens on the target sink.
#
# Match by the backing PLATFORM device (omap-hdmi-audio.1.auto), NOT the ALSA
# card index: the card number is probe-order dependent (HDMI was card1 on one
# boot, card2 on another), and a KERNEL=="cardN" pin matched the wrong card and
# left HDMI un-ignored (v1.6.9-rc1 reject). KERNELS= walks the parent chain to
# the stable platform name. Verified live: tags only the HDMI card, not
# Loopback/tas5713.
SUBSYSTEM=="sound", KERNEL=="card*", KERNELS=="omap-hdmi-audio.1.auto", ENV{PULSE_IGNORE}="1"

# Also ignore the snd-aloop Loopback card. It is INTERNAL ALSA plumbing, not a
# user sink: librespot/audio play into `nexusq_soft` (asound.conf) which routes
# through the Loopback, and the companion bridge taps the Loopback capture side
# at the ALSA level. When PA auto-loads module-alsa-card for it, PA (a) exposes a
# bogus "Loopback Analog Stereo" sink that, being card index 0 on some boots,
# became the DEFAULT sink so desktop audio went into the loopback instead of the
# speaker, and (b) can hold the Loopback playback device, risking EBUSY against
# the librespot→speaker / tap chain. Tag PULSE_IGNORE so the ONLY PA sink is the
# TAS5713 speaker (deterministic default regardless of probe-order card index).
# Same platform-name match rationale as HDMI above (card index is unstable:
# Loopback has been card0 with tas5713/HDMI shuffling around it across boots).
SUBSYSTEM=="sound", KERNEL=="card*", KERNELS=="snd_aloop.0", ENV{PULSE_IGNORE}="1"

# And the SECOND aloop instance (snd_aloop.1 = the RoonLoop card, index 7): it is
# Roon's private playback device inside the bwrap sandbox; PulseAudio touches it
# ONLY via the explicit module-alsa-source on its capture side (loaded by
# roon-nexusq). Without this ignore, PA's udev-detect auto-loads module-alsa-card
# on it and HOLDS the playback substream — RAATServer then gets EBUSY and reports
# DeviceOpenFailed for every enable attempt (hit live 2026-07-17).
SUBSYSTEM=="sound", KERNEL=="card*", KERNELS=="snd_aloop.1", ENV{PULSE_IGNORE}="1"
